> If you just need to see if the logs were created, you can set `"audit_logs_export_endpoint": "RABBIT_MQ"` and check the logs from the search service.
@Sayan this should be sufficient for you, right? you will need to run `search-tservice` in your crafting env and just check if the audit logs are propagated to search service properly
Following up on this, on crafting, I can actually see the correct logs. Thanks for your help @Xindi Xu++ ! Here's the command I used: `cs logs -f search-service | grep APP_DEPLOYMENT_RUN_OPERATION`
